ENTRY       EC 6.3.2.39                 Enzyme
NAME        aerobactin synthase;
            iucC (gene name)
CLASS       Ligases;
            Forming carbon-nitrogen bonds;
            Acid-D-amino-acid ligases (peptide synthases)
SYSNAME     N2-citryl-N6-acetyl-N6-hydroxy-L-lysine:N6-acetyl-N6-hydroxy-L-lysine ligase (ADP-forming)
REACTION    2 ATP + N2-citryl-N6-acetyl-N6-hydroxy-L-lysine + N6-acetyl-N6-hydroxy-L-lysine + H2O = 2 ADP + 2 phosphate + aerobactin [RN:R10091]
ALL_REAC    R10091
SUBSTRATE   ATP [CPD:C00002];
            N2-citryl-N6-acetyl-N6-hydroxy-L-lysine [CPD:C20333];
            N6-acetyl-N6-hydroxy-L-lysine [CPD:C03955];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     ADP [CPD:C00008];
            phosphate [CPD:C00009];
            aerobactin [CPD:C05554]
COMMENT     Requires Mg2+. Aerobactin is one of a group of high-affinity iron chelators known as siderophores and is produced under conditions of iron deprivation [6]. It is a dihydroxamate comprising two molecules of N6-acetyl-N6-hydroxy-L-lysine and one molecule of citric acid. This enzyme catalyses the second of two synthase reactions to link N6-acetyl-N6-hydroxy-L-lysine and citrate [3,4,5].
HISTORY     EC 6.3.2.39 created 2012
